Parent: DT‑502/503/504 CSYS: PSRU_Out_CSYS (origin at mast pilot, X→mast axis)
Datums: A=PSRU output face • B=LH mount pad • C=lower pad

A. Mechanical Interface
Feature	Requirement
Mast seat & pilot	Seat Ø 88.90 mm [3.500 in] (mast OD), pilot depth 12 mm; coaxiality ≤0.03 mm to axis
Spline (TBD)	Placeholder: 30T, 16/32DP involute, fit class K; keyless clamp collar
Fastening	Clamp collar M10‑1.5 (x6) on Ø155 mm; torque 40 N·m; witness marks required
Output speed	430 rpm nominal
Torque ratings	≥4,750 N·m (3,500 lbf·ft) continuous, 7,125 N·m (5,250 lbf·ft) proof (10 s)
Overrunning clutch	Integrated; back‑drive drag ≤10 N·m at 430 rpm; freewheel threshold ≤ 0.5% overspeed
Rotor brake disc	Disc Ø 305 mm [12.0 in], thickness 6.0 mm [0.24 in]; 6× M8‑1.25 on Ø180 mm to PSRU cover
Caliper bracket	2× M10‑1.5 to PSRU boss; pad sweep fully on disc; clearance to housing ≥3 mm
Flatness & position	A flatness ≤0.03 mm; spline pitch dia runout ≤0.02 mm
B. Sensors / Provisions

Speed pickup port M12×1.0 with 0.8 mm tooth target gap; torque meter port M14×1.5 (plugged).

C. Parameter Bindings

drivetrain.mast_od_in, drivetrain.psru_out_rpm, drivetrain.psru_torque_lbf_ft_cont, drivetrain.orc_drag_Nm, drivetrain.brake_disc_D_mm

D. Deliverables

CAD + STEP; drawing/PMI with spline data sheet; brake disc drawing; ORC drag curve; stop‑time calc; mass CSV.

E. Acceptance Tests

Spline gage fit; blueing check ≥85% contact.

ORC drag test @ 430 rpm: ≤10 N·m.

Brake stop from idle Nr to 0 ≤ 15 s ×3 cycles; inspect for fade/heat spotting.

Proof torque 7,125 N·m hold 10 s; no permanent deformation.

Assumptions & Notes: Spline form finalized after supplier DFM; disc Ø can grow if caliper family changes.
